**Water**

The river is very short and the water level in it goes up and down extremely fast. [The online gauge](http://saih.chminosil.es/index.php?url=/datos/ficha/estacion:N019/area:HID) should read approximately 3-10 cumecs. The river is actually bigger here due to the right tributary after the gauge. At 3-5 cumecs on the gauge it''s class IV. At 15 and more cumecs on the gauge it''s class V+

_Mike Krutyansky, 2017_', 'After rains', '', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.291805+00', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.291805+00');

**Water**

It''s hard to get a proper water level here. 4-8 cumecs is ok. This is kind of a section that can definitely be too high. It rises and drops really fast with rain. Don''t put in if it''s raining really hard even if the level looks low. There are two rocks in the river 10 meters upstream the take out bridge. The perfect level is when they are just about to be awashed. If they are really dry it''s low and if you can''t see them it''s too high. It''s still runnable at really low flow but it''s not much fun. The perfect timing is 1-2 day after a rainfall or when there is a little rain.

**The run**

Everything is easy to scout but not everything is easy to portage. There is a lot of scouting needed.

The section starts from a roman foot bridge just after a waterfall and a river-wide syphon. It starts with a steep boulder garden rapid with some syphons. The waterfall combo comes shortly. Don''t put in if the first 100 meters seem too hard!

The main attraction of this section is tripple drop combo (4, 6-7 and 4-5 meters). The pools between the drops are big enough and the drops are quite fair and clean. Soon after the drops the river splits into few channels. Scout this part from the left down to the foot bridge. At certain water levels it''s better to portage.

Soon after this footbridge the river enters a small canyon. The first rapid of the canyon has a huge towback a high flows. The following ones are alright although some of them are very hard to portage. There is a portage (class VI) at the exit of the small canyon just 50 meters upstream the take out bridge.

**Access**

_Put in._ After you are parked at the entrance of the Porta Cova village follow the road down to the left. After the road narrows to a foot path follow the biggest path. There will be two intersections - take left on the first one and right down to the river on the second one. It''s well visiable on Google maps. It''s a 15 minutes hike.

_Note:_ Second run is a lot of fun if you liked the first!

_Mike Krutyansky, 2017_', 'After rain', '1-3 days after rainfall. It shouldn''t be too much!', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.299203+00', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.299203+00');

If the upper is too high or you don''t want to paddle it you can still run something today. The run shouldn''t take more than 30 minutes and you can repeat it again and again.

After the confluence with Otta you will be able to enjoy some big waves surfing. Don''t miss these waves! The take out is at the "Eurowave". The wave or the hole that was once popular for playboating.

