The Chicamocha River is born by the confluence of theTuta River that is born in the town of the same name and the Jordan River.

The put in village of Cepita is located one and a half hours away from San Gil. You can do one or two days depending on how deep you want to get lost in the nature.

It''s possible to paddle the whole section in 4 hours at medium flow.

Starting paddling from Cepita you will have 1.5 hours of class 3 and 3+ (low and medium water level, high water pretty much flat) to get to the Pescadero bridge. It''s the bridge of the main road connecting San Gil and Bucaramanga.

After the brigde there is a big flat section for at least 45 minutes (middle level). Then you reach the bridge of Jordan a place where you can get a coold beer, lunch, place for sleeping. Or just walk to the road and transport yourself to an incredibly beautiful 1800 meters high area.

Once you are back to the river you meet the Cajon rapid soon, which is the best representation of Chicamocha wate whitewater character.

For the next two hours you will like all the scenaries and rapids that will come on the way until you reach the take out place called Raspa-Culos. It''s here where Chicamocha and Suarez become one well-known river Sogamoso which was affected by the construction of a hydro-electric power station.

In this mind-blowing place with two deep canyons you want to have a car already waiting for you.

**Access**

To get at the Cepita town or brigde you can hire a transport in San Gil and you can use the same one to pick you up in Villanueva the same day or next day. To get from the take out to Villanueva you have to hire a proper 4-wheel drive.

**Water**

Mostly of time it looks like brown or black because of sediment.

To check the water level go to Malecon area (where most of rafting companies are) and ask them. You can also call to Exploradores Colombia. +57 304 670 0025 (what''s app)

