В 2013 году в результате катастрофического наводнения Алакнанда очень сильно изменилась. Старые описания больше неактуальны. Местные каякеры говорят, что река стала существенно проще.

В ноябре вода Алакнанды прозрачна и имеет нежно-зеленый оттенок. Вся секция от начала до конца – это веселый аквапарк, состоящий из недлинных, но очень интересных порогов, разделенных неутомительными участками спокойной воды. Уверенные в себе каякеры могут ехать всё без просмотра, остальным лучше посмотреть пару порогов в районе города Чамоли и один напротив тюрьмы (ее и сам порог видно с дороги при заброске). Отличные виды в качестве бонуса.

В большую воду секция становится сложнее на полбалла – балл.', '', '', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.372556+00', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.372556+00');

**Water**

It''s a steep river without a dam and it starts at a big plateau. It stays with enough water for paddling for more than 8 days after the rainfall. Very often there are small local rains or some snowmelt in Peneda mountains. Due to these facts you can head to Castro Laboreiro when everything else is low. On the other side it''s almost the only river in the region that has too much water quite often in winter. So don''t come here when other rivers have a lot of water.

There is a gauge at the put in bridge. Low water is 2.0 and high water is 2.35. There are also green and red marks. The water should be between two green ones. 2.4 is paddleable but it''s very demanding without knowing the river.

**The run**

Everything is possible to scout and to portage. Some portages are quite hard though.

The section starts with flat water in the forest. After some time you reach first small drop and after it the main section of upper Castro Laboreiro begins. Scout the first long bedrock rapid from the right. It''s probably the hardest rapid of the section (except the portages).

The following bedrock rapids are all clean, fair and fun: a tricky slide, the 5 meters "Back-breaker", a narrow channel and another small drop. Be very carefull at high water with eddies after the "Back-breaker"! There are not many but they exist. Immediately after the last small drop the portage on the right begins.

The second portage follows just after the first one. It''s quite a hard portage on the right. This drop has been run by Eric Deguil.

All the rest of the section is class IV boulder gardens with some minor syphons. It''s very bony and not nice with the water level under 2.2 and fun above.

**Access**

The take out is a tiny foot bridge. Depending on your car you can leave it 10 minutes walk away or drive close. If you car is not small better leave it at the last loop of the serpantine.

The valley is quite open and there is a foot path on the left bank.

_Note 1:_ Wear good shoes!

_Note 2:_ You can combine this section with the lower one if you are a very strong and fast crew and if you start really early. Or if you remeber the lines.

