This section is your second last class IV-V option (after Oitaven) in the area when everything is drying out. But be carefull if it’s raining hard because the river rises very fast and the online gauge is far downstream. At low flows 2 rapids require portaging.

**The run**

The run starts with class II-III paddling for few minutes. After another turn couple warm up class IV rapids follow and very soon you reach the crux part of the run. This crux is sequence of 3 class IV+ - V rapids. At certain water levels it’s worth to portage 1-2 of them. At low water the syphon in the first one is harder to avoid.

After the third hard and steep rapid you will find a lot of nice clean and sometimes technical rapids. Some of them require scouting.

The bridge of the main road is the alternative take out. But stay on the river! There are 3 really nice rapids downstream!

Take out at the artificial steps to cross the river before a dam.

_Note:_ If it was way to easy for you and the water level is medium scout the following class V damed gorge.



