Muksu is born at the confluence of few rivers coming from glaciers from three peaks of more than 7 thousand meters and many smaller ones. The main source is the famous Fedchenko glacier coming all the way down to the valley you will be paddling. From this place there is around 30 minutes to reach the road from Kyrgistan coming all the way down to a meteo station. Don''t stop here and avoid the boarder forces. Another couple hours of flat water paddling will bring you to the start of the rapids. 70-80 cumecs here is the reasonable maximum for the canyons that follow.

