The river bed is cut in granite providing paddlers with clean steep rapids sometimes spoiled by chaotic rocks in the middle. The are a lot of dangerous potholes in the rock so take care!

All the rapids are easy to scout and portage. Depending on the water level the difficulty of the rapids vary from IV to V with one class V+ double drop

The river can be done as a two days trip or as two one day trips. There is a ferry in the middle with a trail descending to it

**Water level**

There are big dams on this river. Usually Kopili is not too high.

