There are no portages at proper flow.

The run takes 5-7 hours and there are some steep rapids at the end that require scouting.

There are big flat parts in the beginning, in the middle and at the very end.

**Water level**

The river is full of dams so it''s kind of hard to predict the water level. You start paddling from the power station and 15-25 cumecs just after the put in is a good flow. At the end the river will have double flow because of tributaries.

**Access:** The average speed on the road to the put in is 20 km/h. It''s almost impossible to drive there in a high car because of brunches. You need a 4x4 or just a car with big clearance if it''s dry.

